WEBVTT

00:05.396 --> 00:08.007
[dramatic music]

00:25.808 --> 00:30.291
[keyboard clicking]
[dramatic music]

00:30.378 --> 00:31.727
- [Sammy] "I Love Us."

00:33.120 --> 00:34.860
When I first heard those words,

00:34.947 --> 00:36.166
I thought they were
the corniest three little words

00:36.253 --> 00:38.342
I ever heard in my life.

00:39.691 --> 00:40.779
- You like it?

00:42.216 --> 00:43.391
- I love it.

00:43.478 --> 00:45.480
- [Sammy] I love us,
who says that?

00:45.567 --> 00:47.699
- I know it's not much, but--

00:47.786 --> 00:49.875
- I don't need a ring
to know how you feel.

00:49.962 --> 00:51.834
I don't need anything.

00:51.921 --> 00:54.010
That look in your eyes
says it all.

00:54.097 --> 00:56.578
- Deposit's non-refundable.

00:56.665 --> 00:58.101
- We'll take it.

00:58.188 --> 00:59.842
- If you would have
told me five years ago,

00:59.929 --> 01:01.931
those three little words would
be the most important words

01:02.018 --> 01:04.325
in my life one day,
I would have told you

01:04.412 --> 01:05.456
three other little words.

01:05.543 --> 01:07.110
Shut the fuck up!

01:07.197 --> 01:09.156
Well, technically four.

01:09.243 --> 01:11.201
- What?
I'm just saying, Sammy.

01:11.288 --> 01:14.291
This fucking guy should've
been closed an hour ago.

01:14.378 --> 01:15.640
We're sitting here
like a bunch of yutzes

01:15.727 --> 01:18.208
waiting for these fucking
love birds to split.

01:18.295 --> 01:20.558
Gotta piss so bad
I can taste it.

01:20.645 --> 01:22.691
- Are you finished?

01:22.777 --> 01:25.563
- I'm just saying, we could've
been in and out already.

01:25.650 --> 01:27.217
- Waiting is part
of the business, Richie.

01:27.304 --> 01:29.089
- Yeah, waiting.

01:29.176 --> 01:31.439
Waiting, I mean, one minute
we're cocked and loaded

01:31.526 --> 01:32.788
and the next minute
we're watching

01:32.875 --> 01:35.356
some fucking asshole
overcompensating

01:35.443 --> 01:37.358
with his sidepiece
for an hour?

01:37.445 --> 01:40.360
- One minute can
change everything.

01:40.448 --> 01:44.146
Just so we're clear,
this mook is not my partner.

01:44.234 --> 01:46.235
We're not even friends.
He's an associate.

01:46.323 --> 01:48.369
An over-glorified co-worker.

01:48.456 --> 01:50.414
Okay, here he goes.

01:50.501 --> 01:51.937
Bring the car around.

01:52.024 --> 01:53.156
All right, five minutes.

01:53.243 --> 01:55.723
Right out front
and five minutes.

01:55.811 --> 01:57.508
- I heard you, five minutes.

01:57.595 --> 02:00.207
[dramatic music]

02:01.947 --> 02:04.080
[car door clunking]
[dramatic music]

02:04.167 --> 02:06.604
- [Sammy] I don't like blood
and for a job like this,

02:06.691 --> 02:08.170
there's no need for any.

02:08.258 --> 02:11.043
[car engine roaring]
[dramatic music]

02:11.131 --> 02:12.567
So I bring this box.

02:12.654 --> 02:14.134
[dramatic music]

02:14.221 --> 02:16.353
[glass door clunking]

02:16.440 --> 02:17.398
[dramatic music]

02:18.964 --> 02:20.444
- We're closed!

02:20.531 --> 02:21.750
[dramatic music]

02:21.837 --> 02:23.447
Leave it at the door!

02:23.534 --> 02:25.841
- [Sammy] Nobody pisses their
pants at the sight of a box.

02:25.928 --> 02:27.625
Everybody loves boxes.

02:27.712 --> 02:30.062
It reminds them of their
birthdays or Christmas.

02:30.150 --> 02:32.108
Everybody loves Christmas.

02:32.195 --> 02:34.545
- You're lucky I'm still here.

02:34.632 --> 02:36.329
- [Sammy] A gun, though,
has a very different

02:36.417 --> 02:38.853
and specific effect on people.

02:38.941 --> 02:40.725
Nobody likes guns, especially
when they're pointed

02:40.812 --> 02:42.118
at their fat belly.

02:42.204 --> 02:47.123
[dramatic music]

02:58.308 --> 03:00.354
The difference between
a good thief and a hack

03:00.441 --> 03:02.704
is simple--greed.

03:02.791 --> 03:04.706
You get greedy, you get sloppy.

03:04.793 --> 03:08.231
[dramatic music]

03:08.318 --> 03:09.493
[zip whooshing]

03:09.841 --> 03:14.411
We could've cleaned this guy out
and kept the change,

03:14.498 --> 03:18.154
but the job is the safe,
so that's all we're taking.

03:18.241 --> 03:20.896
[dramatic music]

03:23.115 --> 03:23.855
[zip whooshes]

03:23.942 --> 03:26.597
[dramatic music]

03:33.517 --> 03:34.692
And what's the difference
between a good thief

03:34.779 --> 03:35.998
and a great one?

03:37.781 --> 03:38.740
The getaway.

03:38.827 --> 03:40.132
[dramatic music]

03:40.220 --> 03:42.352
[tires screeching]

03:42.439 --> 03:45.225
[suspenseful dramatic music]

04:16.298 --> 04:18.867
[sirens wailing]

04:40.192 --> 04:42.238
[wailing continues,
brakes squeal]

04:47.243 --> 04:48.418
[bell chimes]

04:48.766 --> 04:51.291
[bus engine roaring]

04:53.641 --> 04:54.859
I wasn't kidding when
I said that one minute

04:54.946 --> 04:56.774
could change everything,

04:57.906 --> 04:59.995
but I was wrong.

05:00.082 --> 05:02.084
It only took a second.

05:02.171 --> 05:02.911
Hey.

05:04.869 --> 05:05.653
- Hey.

05:07.698 --> 05:10.875
- She could have trademarked
that smile.

05:10.962 --> 05:12.050
Wanna get off?

05:13.095 --> 05:15.010
- No, uh...

05:15.097 --> 05:16.794
I'm not that type of girl,
sorry.

05:16.881 --> 05:20.102
- No, no, not get off.
You wanna get off the bus?

05:20.189 --> 05:22.974
Maybe we can get some dinner?

05:23.061 --> 05:24.715
- Can't.

05:24.802 --> 05:26.543
Girl's gotta work.

05:26.630 --> 05:28.197
- Work, now?

05:28.284 --> 05:29.067
- Yeah.

05:30.852 --> 05:32.114
You?

05:32.201 --> 05:33.898
- I just got off work.

05:34.943 --> 05:35.813
- Lucky you.

05:38.207 --> 05:40.383
- Lucky was an understatement.

05:40.470 --> 05:42.211
Where do you work?

05:42.298 --> 05:44.822
- Vincent's.
- Vincent's?

05:45.780 --> 05:47.347
Waitress?

05:47.433 --> 05:48.217
- Yeah.

05:48.304 --> 05:51.263
[bus engine roaring]

05:53.570 --> 05:56.051
- What time are you
getting off?

05:56.138 --> 05:58.401
- [laughs] 10.

05:58.488 --> 05:59.271
- 10?

06:01.186 --> 06:03.275
Maybe I'll come after dinner.
I love Vincent's.

06:03.363 --> 06:05.103
I hate Vincent's.

06:05.974 --> 06:09.325
An Italian restaurant with
nothing but non Italians.

06:09.412 --> 06:11.283
They can cook some
pretty incredible shit,

06:11.371 --> 06:14.461
but nobody messes up a plate
of pasta like Vincent's.

06:14.548 --> 06:18.247
- Hi. What can I get you?

06:18.334 --> 06:22.382
Ooh, the caprese.
Great choice.

06:22.469 --> 06:24.209
Fettuccine, no problem.
And for you?

06:24.296 --> 06:26.560
- The food might be
a nightmare,

06:26.647 --> 06:29.345
but the service is
an absolute dream.

06:29.432 --> 06:30.999
Hey!

06:31.086 --> 06:31.913
- [whispers] I said 10.

06:33.044 --> 06:34.045
- [whispers] 10?

06:34.132 --> 06:35.003
Okay.

06:35.090 --> 06:36.439
[smooth jazz music]

06:44.316 --> 06:45.100
- Hi.

06:48.886 --> 06:52.455
So tell me, what is it
that you do, Sammy?

06:52.542 --> 06:53.761
- Me?
- Mm-hmm.

06:53.848 --> 06:54.718
- I'm a thief.

06:56.111 --> 06:57.591
I'm a diamond dealer.

06:57.678 --> 06:58.896
- Ooh.

06:58.983 --> 07:00.071
Girl's best friend.

07:00.158 --> 07:01.551
- That's right.
- [chuckles]

07:02.596 --> 07:05.425
- Well, looks like you enjoy
the finer things in life.

07:05.512 --> 07:07.035
- That's also right.

07:08.297 --> 07:11.300
- But why did you
take the bus?

07:11.387 --> 07:12.823
Too many DUIs?

07:12.910 --> 07:15.913
- No, no, no, no, nothing
serious like that, no.

07:16.000 --> 07:18.481
Having to lie to her
tore me apart even then.

07:18.568 --> 07:21.702
Car's in the shop,
engine trouble.

07:21.789 --> 07:23.965
- Really?
- [Sammy] Yeah.

07:24.052 --> 07:26.315
- Me too, suspension.

07:26.402 --> 07:27.925
- Look at that.

07:28.012 --> 07:29.187
- You know what
they call that?

07:29.274 --> 07:30.319
- [Sammy] What?

07:30.406 --> 07:31.799
- Serendipity.

07:32.930 --> 07:33.975
- Serendipity.

07:36.020 --> 07:38.414
Well, here's to serendipity.

07:38.501 --> 07:39.241
- Cheers.

07:40.284 --> 07:41.461
- Cheers, Laura.

07:42.549 --> 07:44.289
Fenton, right?

07:44.376 --> 07:46.770
- That's right. [laughs]
Whoo, what a day.

07:49.425 --> 07:51.034
- Need some money?

07:51.122 --> 07:52.994
- Yeah, I mean, a little bit.

07:53.081 --> 07:55.823
- Okay, well,
you look good doing it.

07:58.086 --> 07:59.566
"I Love Us."

07:59.653 --> 08:01.393
[upbeat music]

08:01.481 --> 08:02.830
I didn't know it then,

08:02.917 --> 08:05.223
but that was the beginning
of my life.

08:05.310 --> 08:06.921
♪ Speak of yourself ♪

08:07.008 --> 08:09.706
♪ All over me, will you,
please? ♪

08:09.793 --> 08:11.360
♪ Keep doing your thing ♪

08:11.447 --> 08:14.450
♪ It's fascinating to me ♪

08:14.537 --> 08:16.017
♪ Lost in your eyes ♪

08:16.104 --> 08:18.585
♪ You are the spark
to my flame ♪

08:18.672 --> 08:20.674
♪ In this moment like now ♪

08:20.761 --> 08:25.330
♪ We are like one
and the same ♪

08:25.417 --> 08:26.767
In the next few months,
I showed her

08:26.854 --> 08:28.682
where to get real Italian food.

08:28.769 --> 08:29.813
[upbeat music]

08:29.900 --> 08:31.467
- [Laura] Thank you.

08:31.554 --> 08:34.164
- And she showed me how to
stop looking over my shoulder.

08:34.251 --> 08:38.082
♪ I know where ♪

08:38.169 --> 08:40.998
- But just like anything else
worthwhile in this world,

08:41.085 --> 08:42.565
a new life wasn't
gonna come easy.

08:42.652 --> 08:45.525
[upbeat music]

08:45.612 --> 08:47.396
[Laura laughs]
[upbeat music]

08:47.483 --> 08:48.223
- Ticklish.

08:48.310 --> 08:49.137
- I love it.

08:49.224 --> 08:52.444
♪ You know me ♪

08:52.532 --> 08:58.712
♪ It won't be long ♪

08:59.887 --> 09:02.759
♪ On the dance floor ♪

09:07.372 --> 09:08.504
- You okay?

09:08.591 --> 09:11.376
- [sighs]

09:11.463 --> 09:12.943
Um...

09:15.772 --> 09:19.210
- You remember I told
you about my husband?

09:19.297 --> 09:20.037
- Yeah.

09:22.518 --> 09:25.260
Pancreatic cancer,
what a shitshow.

09:26.914 --> 09:29.090
She said he didn't go
without a fight,

09:29.177 --> 09:31.527
and they fought it right
through the end.

09:31.614 --> 09:33.964
That was nine years ago,

09:34.051 --> 09:35.792
but I could tell
she was still fighting.

09:35.879 --> 09:37.881
- There's something
that I haven't told you.

09:37.968 --> 09:41.450
[dramatic music]

09:41.537 --> 09:42.930
- You don't have to do that,
Laura.

09:43.017 --> 09:45.540
- No. Here.

09:45.672 --> 09:48.675
[dramatic music]

09:49.501 --> 09:53.505
If you wanna see how this goes,
it's in those photos.

09:53.593 --> 09:56.247
[dramatic music]

09:58.685 --> 10:00.774
Listen, I...

10:01.949 --> 10:04.212
This has been great.

10:04.299 --> 10:06.475
I've had an amazing time,

10:06.562 --> 10:10.479
I don't remember the last time
I've laughed so much,

10:10.566 --> 10:14.178
but I'm not interested
in wasting anyone's time

10:15.266 --> 10:19.140
and...if this is, um...

10:19.227 --> 10:21.882
if this is a problem for you...

10:21.969 --> 10:23.057
[inhales and exhales deeply]

10:23.144 --> 10:25.146
um, I understand.

10:25.233 --> 10:27.888
[dramatic music]

10:29.367 --> 10:30.151
- No.

10:32.457 --> 10:33.807
They're beautiful.

10:35.809 --> 10:37.506
I wanna see where this goes.

10:37.593 --> 10:39.160
Really do.

10:39.247 --> 10:42.859
[dramatic music]

10:42.946 --> 10:44.687
I love you.

10:47.821 --> 10:50.171
You're so beautiful.
- Thank you.

10:50.388 --> 10:51.215
- [Sammy] Who is this one?

10:51.302 --> 10:52.869
- This is Rachel.

10:52.956 --> 10:54.262
- She looks like you.

10:54.349 --> 10:55.393
- [Laura] And that's Audrey.

10:55.480 --> 10:58.527
[dramatic music]

10:58.614 --> 11:00.181
- I'm here.

11:00.268 --> 11:02.487
For the long run.

11:02.574 --> 11:05.229
- Thank you.

11:05.316 --> 11:08.276
- [Sammy] Love makes you
say some stupid shit, right?

11:08.363 --> 11:10.974
But at least
I wasn't lying to her.

11:26.947 --> 11:28.470
- [Sammy] Thank you.

11:33.083 --> 11:34.737
- So, are you Italian?

11:36.347 --> 11:38.262
- No, everyone asks me that.

11:38.349 --> 11:40.438
I'm actually Israeli.

11:40.525 --> 11:43.790
- Sammy, he's actually
from Brooklyn.

11:43.877 --> 11:44.834
- New York?

11:44.921 --> 11:46.880
- Yeah, have you guys ever been?

11:46.967 --> 11:47.968
- No.

11:48.925 --> 11:51.972
- Dad always wanted to go
to New York.

11:52.059 --> 11:54.757
- Yes, yes, he did.

11:57.978 --> 11:59.196
- You're a lot shorter
than dad.

11:59.283 --> 12:00.937
- Rachel!
- [Rachel] What?

12:01.024 --> 12:02.809
- No, no, no,
it's totally fine.

12:02.896 --> 12:06.290
Yeah, uh, I'm a lot shorter
than a lot of people.

12:08.379 --> 12:10.294
- Go set the dinner table,
please.

12:15.125 --> 12:15.865
Now!

12:16.910 --> 12:19.390
[Rachel sighs]

12:24.395 --> 12:25.222
I'm so sorry.

12:25.309 --> 12:27.616
- No, Laura, it's fine, no.

12:27.703 --> 12:30.445
I'm sure it's not easy
on them.

12:30.532 --> 12:31.707
- You're sweet.

12:33.143 --> 12:35.493
I'm gonna go check on dinner.

12:37.713 --> 12:38.453
Rachel!

12:47.549 --> 12:48.463
- This is delicious.

12:48.550 --> 12:49.725
Really is.

12:49.812 --> 12:51.596
- Well, I'm so glad
you like it.

12:51.683 --> 12:53.555
- Like it? I love it.

12:53.642 --> 12:55.252
- It's just meatloaf.

12:56.645 --> 12:59.387
- This meatloaf,
it's a masterpiece.

13:00.388 --> 13:02.303
- Mom's meatloaf is lit.

13:02.390 --> 13:04.000
- Meatloaf can't be lit.

13:04.087 --> 13:05.306
- Yes, it can.

13:06.263 --> 13:08.178
- No it can't.
That doesn't make sense.

13:08.265 --> 13:10.311
- It means it's really good.

13:10.398 --> 13:12.182
- I know what it means.
- There's no competition.

13:12.269 --> 13:14.576
It's the best meatloaf
I've ever had in my life.

13:14.663 --> 13:15.316
- The best.
- Mm.

13:16.752 --> 13:17.797
- And so are you.
- Mm.

13:21.104 --> 13:23.150
- Well, wait till you taste
dessert. We made cupcakes.

13:23.237 --> 13:25.326
- That's exactly what you need,
Audrey, more cupcakes.

13:25.413 --> 13:27.632
- [Audrey] Shut up.
- [Laura] Girls.

13:29.896 --> 13:31.506
- Make sure not to get
too many crumbs on mom

13:31.593 --> 13:33.813
while you're kissing her ass.

13:34.726 --> 13:36.772
- Rachel!

13:38.165 --> 13:39.296
I'm sorry.

13:39.383 --> 13:41.908
- No, no, no, that's fine.

13:41.995 --> 13:43.692
It's fine.

13:43.779 --> 13:46.477
Cheers, guys.
Thank you for having me.

13:46.564 --> 13:47.696
- Thank you.

13:47.783 --> 13:49.045
Cheers.

13:49.132 --> 13:50.481
- Nice meeting you, Audrey.

13:50.568 --> 13:52.440
- You, too.

13:55.269 --> 13:56.531
- You're really brave,
you know that?

13:56.618 --> 13:58.750
[insects chirping]

13:58.838 --> 13:59.534
- Really?
- Mm-hmm.

14:00.840 --> 14:02.406
- I guess.

14:02.493 --> 14:04.234
- I'm serious.

14:05.714 --> 14:07.281
It can't be easy for you either.

14:07.368 --> 14:09.892
[insects chirping]

14:09.979 --> 14:12.112
- I mean, I must seem
like an intruder

14:12.199 --> 14:14.070
to these girls, right?

14:14.157 --> 14:15.506
- Well...

14:15.593 --> 14:16.638
they'll be fine.

14:16.725 --> 14:18.466
It's just gonna take some time.

14:18.553 --> 14:20.381
[insects chirping]

14:20.468 --> 14:22.383
- I thought they were gonna
fall in love with me

14:22.470 --> 14:23.993
in first sight,
just like you did.

14:24.080 --> 14:25.821
[Audrey and Rachel laughing]

14:25.908 --> 14:28.563
- You know, on the bus,
when I first saw you,

14:28.650 --> 14:31.479
I kind of thought
you were a creep.

14:31.566 --> 14:32.175
- A creep?
- [laughs]

14:33.394 --> 14:35.483
- Really?
- I did.

14:35.570 --> 14:36.614
You're lucky I didn't
have my other purse

14:36.701 --> 14:38.834
with my pepper spray and taser.

14:38.921 --> 14:40.096
- Ooh, pepper spray.

14:40.183 --> 14:40.923
- Yeah.

14:42.925 --> 14:44.971
- Yeah, you're right, I am.

14:46.146 --> 14:47.843
- You are what?

14:47.930 --> 14:49.497
- Lucky.

14:50.846 --> 14:52.804
- Yeah, you are.
[laughs]

14:53.849 --> 14:55.503
I love them so much.

14:55.590 --> 14:57.418
[Rachel and Audrey laughing]

14:57.505 --> 14:58.810
- And I love you.

15:02.162 --> 15:04.381
- And I love you.

15:04.468 --> 15:06.427
- [Sammy] I could've married
her right then and there.

15:06.514 --> 15:08.255
[upbeat music]

15:08.342 --> 15:11.127
But I married her a year later.

15:11.214 --> 15:14.348
Her mother, who we barely
got up the stairs,

15:14.435 --> 15:16.393
even her junkie brother
was there.

15:16.480 --> 15:18.395
Nice guy, but a hot mess.

15:19.657 --> 15:20.789
In front of her girls.

15:20.876 --> 15:23.618
[upbeat music]

15:24.532 --> 15:26.621
All these people showed up
to see us.

15:26.708 --> 15:29.276
- [Laura] I love us.

15:29.363 --> 15:31.800
- And all I can think about
is that one person who didn't.

15:31.887 --> 15:34.368
[upbeat music]

15:39.721 --> 15:40.591
[knock on door]

15:40.678 --> 15:43.116
[upbeat music]

15:48.251 --> 15:50.123
Hey, Pops, what are you doing?

15:52.734 --> 15:54.910
- That's for the job

15:54.997 --> 15:57.391
and here...

15:57.478 --> 15:59.045
from me.

15:59.306 --> 16:01.003
Wedding gift.

16:02.744 --> 16:04.572
You know, showing up
to the wedding

16:04.659 --> 16:06.574
would have been a good gift,
you know that, right, Pop?

16:06.661 --> 16:08.271
- Uh, don't be so sure.

16:08.358 --> 16:09.620
You haven't seen
what's inside the envelope.

16:09.707 --> 16:13.973
[chuckles] Thank you, Pop.
I appreciate it.

16:14.060 --> 16:14.799
- So...

16:18.238 --> 16:20.196
You're married, huh?

16:20.283 --> 16:21.371
- Look at this.

16:24.331 --> 16:25.767
- I don't know what
your mother would've felt

16:25.897 --> 16:29.466
about you marrying a goya,
but I'm sure the food was good.

16:29.553 --> 16:32.121
The food was great.
Mom would've loved her.

16:32.208 --> 16:36.560
- Maybe. I mean, you know
your mother better than I did.

16:36.647 --> 16:38.040
- You gonna love her too, Pops.

16:38.127 --> 16:40.303
She's awesome. She really is.

16:40.390 --> 16:42.044
- How are the kids?

16:42.131 --> 16:43.785
Ooh. Kids, tough.

16:45.178 --> 16:46.744
Big one, Rachel,
hates my guts.

16:46.831 --> 16:48.920
It's like I killed
her dad myself.

16:49.008 --> 16:51.358
The little one,
Audrey, is really sweet,

16:51.445 --> 16:53.621
but, you know,
it's just tough.

16:53.708 --> 16:56.667
New guy coming in.

16:56.754 --> 16:59.801
At that age, it's not easy.

17:01.020 --> 17:03.587
- Do you want some advice?
- No, no, no, no, no.

17:03.674 --> 17:06.634
- Don't be their friend.
They got friends.

17:06.721 --> 17:09.115
- What part of "I don't want any
advice" don't you understand?

17:09.202 --> 17:12.814
- They don't need a friend.
They need a father.

17:14.858 --> 17:18.385
- Yeah, I guess.
- Here.

17:21.257 --> 17:23.694
This is a good lead.
Take a lock.

17:23.781 --> 17:25.608
Stake it out,
take Richie with you.

17:25.695 --> 17:27.133
- No, no, no, no,
I don't like Richie.

17:27.220 --> 17:29.352
- What's with you and liking
all of a sudden, huh?

17:29.439 --> 17:31.963
You don't have to like him,
all right?

17:32.051 --> 17:33.487
You don't have to go camping
with the guy.

17:33.574 --> 17:35.271
You sit in the back seat,
I told you.

17:35.358 --> 17:37.360
- I do. He doesn't stop
asking questions.

17:37.447 --> 17:40.581
- Well then,
stop answering them then, huh?

17:40.668 --> 17:44.150
- It's very easy to say.
The guy is unbelievable.

17:44.237 --> 17:48.632
- Look, I told you that I'm
gonna look out for you, right?

17:48.719 --> 17:51.113
You bang out a few more jobs,

17:51.200 --> 17:53.594
you'll be square with Ira
before you know it.

17:53.681 --> 17:55.639
- I know, Pops. I appreciate it.
I really do.

17:55.726 --> 17:57.859
It's just,
I can't lie to Laura anymore.

17:57.946 --> 17:58.686
- Lying?

18:00.470 --> 18:01.993
You tell her you work here,
right?

18:02.081 --> 18:03.647
- Yeah, I tell her I work here,
but...

18:03.734 --> 18:07.434
- Well, then... [laughs]
get to work.

18:07.521 --> 18:09.088
- I can't lie to her.

18:09.175 --> 18:11.220
I can't lie to those girls.
I mean, it's...

18:11.394 --> 18:13.266
It's my life now, you know?

18:13.353 --> 18:16.747
- Sammy, I know that
we throw the word job

18:16.834 --> 18:18.401
around here a lot, okay?

18:18.488 --> 18:22.666
But this isn't what you do.
It's who you are.

18:22.753 --> 18:24.277
You want some more advice?

18:24.364 --> 18:25.495
- No, please.

18:25.582 --> 18:27.410
- Just tell her.

18:27.497 --> 18:29.108
You want that life?

18:29.195 --> 18:31.371
You got to come clean.

18:31.458 --> 18:33.242
You build it on a foundation
of bullshit,

18:33.329 --> 18:35.026
that life will come tumbling
down one day,

18:35.114 --> 18:37.203
right on top of your head,

18:37.290 --> 18:40.249
and you won't be able to
do a damn thing about it

18:40.336 --> 18:42.382
except try to take the hit.

18:43.731 --> 18:45.559
- I guess, I don't know.

18:48.910 --> 18:49.693
[Sammy sighing]

18:49.780 --> 18:51.130
I don't know, Pops.

18:53.393 --> 18:55.308
Growing up,
I didn't need a friend either,

18:55.395 --> 18:56.918
but as far as fathers go,

18:57.005 --> 19:00.226
mine definitely made
a better boss.

19:00.313 --> 19:01.705
The name he just dropped,

19:01.792 --> 19:04.665
is why my posture is
so fucked up these days.

19:04.752 --> 19:07.581
[techno music]

19:07.668 --> 19:08.886
Ira Prince.

19:08.973 --> 19:10.061
Great guy,

19:11.280 --> 19:14.065
but Ira always had one hand
in someone's pocket

19:14.153 --> 19:18.461
and another wrapped gently
around their throats

19:18.548 --> 19:21.072
and his grip never felt tighter.

19:22.813 --> 19:24.075
I was a gambler.
Yes!

19:24.163 --> 19:25.512
A good one.
Yes! Yes!

19:25.599 --> 19:28.341
Which means I was also
a bad one.

19:28.428 --> 19:32.475
When I would hit, I would live
it up like a goddamn king.

19:32.562 --> 19:36.262
[upbeat music]
[ladies giggling]

19:36.349 --> 19:39.482
But when I got hit, you've
never seen a sorer loser.

19:39.569 --> 19:41.310
I hate this... [indistinct].

19:41.397 --> 19:43.094
One day I got hit really bad

19:43.182 --> 19:48.056
and I not only lost my money,
I lost my friends' money

19:48.143 --> 19:51.668
and I lost Ira's money.

19:52.060 --> 19:54.976
Ira and my dad go way back,
so as a favor to him,

19:55.063 --> 19:57.761
he took it easy on me.

19:57.848 --> 20:01.200
He agreed to let me pay
him back in installments.

20:01.287 --> 20:03.637
They say that if you do
something for 10,000 hours,

20:03.724 --> 20:05.726
you become a professional,
right?

20:05.813 --> 20:08.250
Well, I became
a fucking professional.

20:08.337 --> 20:10.818
[upbeat music]

20:17.520 --> 20:18.260
[car door clunking]

20:18.347 --> 20:19.957
What do we got?

20:20.044 --> 20:22.133
- Now, why do you have
to seat in the back seat

20:22.221 --> 20:24.310
like I'm your fucking chauffeur?

20:24.397 --> 20:27.530
- Technically, that's what
you are now.

20:27.617 --> 20:29.706
- Technically an asshole
is what you are.

20:29.793 --> 20:31.534
What do we have Richie?
What's going on over here?

20:31.621 --> 20:33.754
Explain to me, please.

20:33.841 --> 20:35.451
I never liked pawn shops.

20:35.538 --> 20:37.801
There's always one idiot
that wants to play the hero.

20:37.888 --> 20:40.848
- That chubby over there,
he comes out for a smoke break

20:40.935 --> 20:44.330
about every 15 minutes.
He's got a partner inside.

20:44.417 --> 20:46.157
That guy comes out at the end
of the day though, all right?

20:46.245 --> 20:48.334
- If I want to put this life
behind me,

20:48.421 --> 20:51.728
I gotta stop thinking small time
and start thinking big time.

20:51.815 --> 20:53.556
- [cellphone buzzes]
- Hey, sweetie.

20:53.643 --> 20:55.602
- [Laura] Um, did you forget
that we have dinner tonight?

20:55.689 --> 20:57.865
- Oh, shit. No, no, no,
uh, I didn't forget.

20:57.952 --> 20:59.562
[Laura] You know that I said
dinner at seven

20:59.649 --> 21:01.999
with the girls, right?
- [Sammy] Laura, I promise.

21:02.086 --> 21:04.175
- [Laura] Okay, I love you.
- I love you too, sweetie.

21:04.263 --> 21:05.873
- [Laura] I'll see you soon.
- Okay.

21:05.960 --> 21:07.744
- I'll be there in a little bit.
- [Laura] Okay, bye.

21:07.831 --> 21:10.878
- Okay, bye. Yo, I gotta go.

21:10.965 --> 21:12.314
Listen, you're doing
a great job.

21:12.401 --> 21:14.185
Keep an eye on them,
and I'll see you tomorrow.

21:14.273 --> 21:15.752
- I thought I was just a driver.

21:15.839 --> 21:17.450
- You are just a driver, Richie.

21:17.537 --> 21:18.407
[car door clunking]

21:18.712 --> 21:20.453
[insects chirping]

21:20.540 --> 21:22.019
This was it.

21:22.106 --> 21:25.849
Time to decide if I play
the friend card or the dad card.

21:25.936 --> 21:27.808
As long as I didn't play
the vomit card.

21:27.895 --> 21:30.767
[insects chirping]

21:30.854 --> 21:34.205
- We're, like, really mean
to him and that's why--

21:34.293 --> 21:35.337
- Dude, how old are you?

21:36.991 --> 21:39.254
- Hey.
- Hey.

21:39.341 --> 21:41.343
- Hi.
- Hi.

21:41.430 --> 21:42.953
- How was your day?
- Good.

21:43.040 --> 21:44.694
- Hi, girls.
- Hi.

21:48.263 --> 21:49.917
- What's with the teddy bear?

21:50.004 --> 21:52.093
- We're having a Teddy talk.

21:52.180 --> 21:54.748
- Shit, I was playing with
the wrong fucking deck.

21:54.835 --> 21:56.053
A Teddy talk?

21:57.098 --> 21:59.796
- Yeah, Teddy.

22:00.536 --> 22:04.061
He helps us get things
off our chests in a safe

22:04.148 --> 22:07.891
and controlled manner.

22:07.978 --> 22:12.896
Also helps us, you know,
with big family announcements.

22:13.201 --> 22:14.768
- Are we gonna go
to Disneyland?

22:14.855 --> 22:16.030
- Audrey, shut up.

22:16.117 --> 22:18.859
- No, we're not going
to Disneyland.

22:20.251 --> 22:22.863
Um...

22:22.950 --> 22:24.604
[sighs]

22:24.691 --> 22:25.387
Listen, um...

22:28.782 --> 22:31.959
I know the last few years, uh,
have been tough.

22:34.483 --> 22:38.313
Well, I've been thinking,
and I've--

22:38.400 --> 22:40.097
- What your mom is trying
to say is--

22:40.184 --> 22:41.403
- Shh!
- This is so dumb.

22:41.490 --> 22:43.362
- Shh!

22:43.449 --> 22:45.973
- You're not allowed to
talk unless you have Teddy.

22:46.060 --> 22:49.019
I'm so sorry. That will
never happen again, please.

22:49.106 --> 22:51.805
- That way everyone is heard,
right?

22:51.892 --> 22:54.460
Without being interrupted.

22:54.547 --> 22:59.508
Anyways, um, Sammy and I,
we have been talking and...

23:01.292 --> 23:03.338
He's my husband now, so--

23:03.425 --> 23:05.384
- Why are you being so weird?

23:05.471 --> 23:06.776
- I'm not being weird.

23:06.863 --> 23:08.038
- [Rachel] You're being
really weird.

23:08.125 --> 23:10.171
- No.

23:10.258 --> 23:13.609
I'm not. I'm... What I'm trying
to say is Sammy and I,

23:13.696 --> 23:17.961
we've been talking,
and, well, I...

23:18.048 --> 23:19.659
he's a part of our family now,

23:19.746 --> 23:23.358
and he's an important part,
and we want... we wanna know

23:24.403 --> 23:28.232
what you feel about him, um,
becoming your father.

23:28.319 --> 23:30.974
[dramatic music]

23:34.500 --> 23:36.284
- Is this a joke?

23:36.371 --> 23:39.069
- No, it's not a joke,
actually, Rach.

23:40.984 --> 23:43.204
- Mom, tell me you're joking.

23:44.988 --> 23:47.382
I wasn't either. I'm not.

23:47.469 --> 23:50.472
[gentle guitar music]

23:52.779 --> 23:54.215
- This is bullshit.

23:56.696 --> 23:58.349
- Sorry. Rachel, Rachel!

23:58.437 --> 24:02.441
[gentle guitar music]

24:02.528 --> 24:05.618
[door slams]

24:05.705 --> 24:06.836
- Shit.

24:06.923 --> 24:08.664
- [giggles]

24:08.751 --> 24:11.754
[gentle guitar music]

24:18.326 --> 24:19.066
You okay?

24:21.764 --> 24:22.896
- I don't know.

24:28.684 --> 24:32.383
Maybe we should've waited
until we moved in together.

24:32.471 --> 24:36.649
You know?
Ease them into it?

24:36.736 --> 24:38.389
- Yeah.

24:40.217 --> 24:42.611
I mean, she misses her dad.

24:42.698 --> 24:44.918
They both do. I get it.

24:45.005 --> 24:45.701
I'm not him.

24:47.573 --> 24:49.879
The application still need
to come in, so...

24:49.966 --> 24:52.360
we'll see what happens.

24:52.447 --> 24:55.450
Well, I made it through that
long ones.

24:57.887 --> 24:58.627
What?

24:58.714 --> 24:59.846
- Yeah, you are.

24:59.933 --> 25:02.979
[giggles]

25:03.066 --> 25:03.893
- Times didn't always suck.

25:03.980 --> 25:06.330
[family cheering]

25:06.417 --> 25:07.549
Sometimes they started to
look up.

25:07.636 --> 25:10.030
- Ah, thank you.
- Well, I'll take it.

25:10.117 --> 25:11.553
- And we started to feel like
a family.

25:11.640 --> 25:14.295
[dramatic music]

25:22.869 --> 25:24.174
[car door clunks]

25:24.261 --> 25:26.916
[dramatic music]

25:30.006 --> 25:31.660
I loved surprising her.

25:33.401 --> 25:37.579
And nothing felt better than
to see her get a new car.

25:37.753 --> 25:39.450
- One more step.
- Okay, okay, okay.

25:39.538 --> 25:40.495
- Step.
- Okay, okay.

25:40.582 --> 25:41.627
- One more.
- Okay, okay.

25:41.714 --> 25:43.106
- Are you ready?
- I think so.

25:43.193 --> 25:45.674
[dramatic music]

25:45.761 --> 25:47.415
Oh, my gosh!

25:47.502 --> 25:49.286
Oh my gosh!
- You like it?

25:49.373 --> 25:52.768
- Sammy, mm! Oh, my gosh,
it's beautiful.

25:52.855 --> 25:54.988
- It's yours.

25:55.075 --> 25:57.468
- Girls, girls, come here!

25:57.556 --> 25:59.340
Oh, my gosh!
- [Sammy] She was so happy.

25:59.427 --> 26:01.385
- Girls, girls, come here!

26:01.472 --> 26:03.170
- Are you serious?
- Oh, my God, Mom!

26:03.257 --> 26:04.650
- And we finally felt like
a family.

26:04.737 --> 26:06.347
You like it?
- Yes!

26:06.434 --> 26:08.523
- Go, go. Go get your shoes on,
go get your shoes on.

26:08.610 --> 26:10.830
- All right, get in, get in.
- Oh, my gosh, oh, my gosh.

26:10.917 --> 26:15.791
- [Sammy] You like it?
- It's beautiful, so beautiful!

26:15.878 --> 26:17.619
- [Sammy] Get in.
- [Audrey] Thank you.

26:17.706 --> 26:19.882
- [Laura] Okay, ladies.

26:19.969 --> 26:21.101
- [Rachel] Where are we going?

26:21.188 --> 26:22.972
- Where to?
- [Sammy] Malibu!

26:23.059 --> 26:24.278
- Ahh!

26:24.365 --> 26:27.324
[car engine roaring]

26:29.718 --> 26:34.201
What a view,
and I don't mean the landscape.

26:34.288 --> 26:36.464
- This is the most amazing car
that I've ever been in.

26:36.551 --> 26:39.510
[upbeat music]

26:39.598 --> 26:40.816
- When are you guys
gonna get your license?

26:40.903 --> 26:43.297
She looked so beautiful
in that car.

26:43.384 --> 26:44.646
Would you let them
drive your car?

26:44.733 --> 26:45.560
[Laura gasps]

26:45.647 --> 26:46.387
- No.

26:46.474 --> 26:47.606
- Wait, why not?

26:47.693 --> 26:50.130
[upbeat music]

26:55.831 --> 26:58.399
- [Sammy] Good night, Audrey.

26:58.486 --> 26:59.792
- Good night, Sammy.

27:01.054 --> 27:02.446
- Sweet dreams, honey.

27:07.190 --> 27:09.845
- He really cares about you,
though.

27:09.932 --> 27:12.500
[knock on door]

27:12.587 --> 27:14.110
- [Sammy] Good night, Rachel.

27:16.765 --> 27:18.680
- [Laura] He's trying to.

27:20.334 --> 27:22.205
- [Rachel] Good night, Mom.

27:25.513 --> 27:27.297
- Good night, sweetheart.

27:31.127 --> 27:32.476
She said to say good night.

27:32.563 --> 27:34.261
- No, she didn't.

27:34.348 --> 27:36.219
- She did.
- No, she didn't.

27:36.306 --> 27:38.613
- [laughs] Okay, no, she didn't,

27:38.700 --> 27:43.487
but maybe you, um,
maybe you wanna tuck me in.

27:43.574 --> 27:45.664
- Mmh, I'll tuck you in.
- Mm-hmm.

27:45.751 --> 27:47.056
- All day, every day.
- [laughs]

27:47.143 --> 27:49.755
[dramatic music]

27:53.367 --> 27:58.459
[dramatic music]

27:59.068 --> 28:01.418
[car door clicking]

28:01.505 --> 28:04.160
[suspenseful dramatic music]

28:04.247 --> 28:05.248
[car door clunking]

28:05.335 --> 28:07.642
[dramatic music]

28:07.729 --> 28:09.209
- Here.

28:09.296 --> 28:10.732
No mustard.

28:10.819 --> 28:12.473
- Thanks.

28:12.560 --> 28:15.084
Richie, you sure there's
only two guys in there?

28:15.171 --> 28:15.868
- Yeah.

28:17.391 --> 28:19.132
- [Sammy] The fat guy looks
like trouble.

28:19.219 --> 28:22.178
You think you can handle him?
- What's there to handle?

28:22.265 --> 28:24.790
I put my gun in his mouth and
tell the fat fuck what's what.

28:24.877 --> 28:26.922
He's gonna understand.

28:28.010 --> 28:31.622
- What are you gonna do if
he tries something stupid?

28:31.710 --> 28:34.016
- Well, then I try something
stupid first.

28:34.103 --> 28:36.323
- Listen, I don't want any
shooting on this this, okay?

28:36.410 --> 28:38.412
Serious.

28:38.499 --> 28:40.457
If he gets out of line,
if he says something stupid,

28:40.544 --> 28:41.937
you talk loud and you hit him
with a fucking gun

28:42.024 --> 28:43.069
over the head.

28:44.548 --> 28:46.333
I heard about what happened
in Atlanta.

28:46.420 --> 28:48.204
I should've had my head
examined sitting in a car

28:48.291 --> 28:51.555
with this guy,
let alone do a job with him.

28:51.642 --> 28:53.644
- [Richie] What'd you hear?

28:53.732 --> 28:55.472
- Enough to know I don't want
any fucking shooting this week.

28:56.822 --> 28:59.259
- It was an accident.

28:59.346 --> 29:02.305
- That's even fucking worse. I'm
actually doing it on purpose.

29:02.392 --> 29:05.482
- You know what? Fuck you,
Sammy, 'cause you weren't there.

29:05.569 --> 29:09.008
- A bad feeling before a job
is never good,

29:09.095 --> 29:11.010
but a full blown sign
from God himself--

29:11.097 --> 29:12.402
- [Richie]
What the fuck you doing?

29:12.489 --> 29:14.187
- That's something else
entirely.

29:14.274 --> 29:14.927
[whispers] Oh, fuck.

29:16.319 --> 29:18.452
Holy shit,
go, go, go, go, go, go!

29:18.539 --> 29:20.106
- What? Why?
- Start the car! Go, go!

29:20.193 --> 29:22.108
Oh, my God.
- And what about your car?

29:22.195 --> 29:24.110
- Go, go, go, go, go.
I'll pick it up later.

29:24.197 --> 29:25.676
- All right, give me a second.
- Go, go.

29:25.764 --> 29:28.505
[car revving]

29:28.592 --> 29:31.247
[dramatic music]

29:33.597 --> 29:36.600
I don't care what the fuck he
said. To me it doesn't matter.

29:38.733 --> 29:40.735
- What's the problem?

29:40.822 --> 29:43.259
- Job's off. I'm not doing it.

29:43.346 --> 29:45.522
- Why not?
- It doesn't feel right.

29:45.609 --> 29:48.438
Something in my gut tells me
not to do this one, Pops.

29:50.440 --> 29:52.573
- Richie, put the napkin down,
please.

29:52.660 --> 29:54.140
- Oh.

29:54.227 --> 29:56.795
- And what does your gut
tell you?

29:56.882 --> 29:58.361
- My gut?

29:58.448 --> 30:00.537
Looks like a piece of cake
to me.

30:00.624 --> 30:02.409
What do I know, right?

30:02.496 --> 30:03.889
- Sammy, do the job.

30:03.976 --> 30:05.673
- I'm not doing the job, Pops,
seriously.

30:05.760 --> 30:06.630
Gotta get me something bigger.

30:06.717 --> 30:08.328
- Bigger?

30:08.415 --> 30:11.679
- Yeah, big enough.
- Ah. Big enough for what?

30:11.766 --> 30:13.376
- Big enough so I don't have
to do this shit anymore,

30:13.463 --> 30:15.509
penny dime shit.

30:15.596 --> 30:19.034
I can't do this. I can't...
I can't lie to Laura anymore.

30:20.383 --> 30:22.081
- So tell her the truth.

30:22.168 --> 30:24.344
- I can't do that.

30:24.431 --> 30:27.260
- Sammy, you're trying
to be a better man, okay?

30:27.347 --> 30:30.176
She can't hate you for that.

30:30.263 --> 30:32.091
- Hold on. Hello?

30:32.178 --> 30:33.701
[Dr. Bule] Sammy Silver,

30:33.788 --> 30:35.834
this is Dr. Bule
from the Medical Center.

30:35.921 --> 30:37.531
There's been an accident.

30:37.618 --> 30:40.664
- And just like that, the world
dropped away from me.

30:40.751 --> 30:45.669
[dramatic music]

30:49.412 --> 30:53.112
[car engine starts]

30:53.199 --> 30:54.461
[dramatic music]

31:15.874 --> 31:18.224
They said the driver was drunk.

31:19.965 --> 31:21.314
She didn't see it coming.

31:21.401 --> 31:23.969
[dramatic music]

31:27.494 --> 31:30.453
For the first time in my life,
I had nothing to say.

31:30.540 --> 31:33.195
[dramatic music]

31:48.863 --> 31:52.432
These girls were
the only thing I had left.

31:52.519 --> 31:54.651
They reminded me of her.

31:54.738 --> 31:57.524
[guitar music]

31:58.525 --> 32:01.615
♪ There's a secret
