33:49.114 --> 33:50.680
I'm trying.

33:50.767 --> 33:53.074
I'm trying to take care of...
I don't know.

33:53.161 --> 33:56.382
♪ Will we ever know? Tell me,
will we, will we ever know? ♪

33:56.469 --> 33:58.297
I'm sorry. I'm so sorry.

33:58.384 --> 34:00.908
[guitar music]

34:00.995 --> 34:02.344
[sighs]

34:14.748 --> 34:15.531
- Sammy?

34:19.274 --> 34:20.014
Sammy.

34:23.713 --> 34:25.411
- Good morning.
- Hi.

34:38.511 --> 34:40.078
Breakfast?

34:40.165 --> 34:42.428
- Mm-hmm.

34:42.514 --> 34:44.212
- All right, sit down,
I'm coming.

34:44.299 --> 34:45.605
- Okay.

34:47.563 --> 34:50.914
[sighing]

35:01.751 --> 35:03.013
How'd you sleep?

35:04.928 --> 35:06.669
- [Audrey] It was okay.

35:08.889 --> 35:09.672
- Eggs?

35:11.413 --> 35:12.110
- Sure.

35:20.292 --> 35:22.120
- Where's your sister?

35:22.207 --> 35:23.817
- She's still asleep.

35:26.472 --> 35:28.300
- Scrambled okay?

35:28.387 --> 35:29.127
- Sure.

35:41.051 --> 35:41.791
Thank you.

35:51.149 --> 35:52.672
- Breakfast?

35:52.759 --> 35:53.499
- Sure.

36:05.685 --> 36:08.122
So, I took the day off
from work.

36:08.209 --> 36:10.211
We can do anything
you guys want.

36:10.298 --> 36:12.822
[cellphone buzzing]

36:14.346 --> 36:16.086
- [Audrey]
Can we go to Disneyland?

36:16.174 --> 36:19.307
- Okay, we got one
for Disneyland.

36:19.394 --> 36:20.961
What are you thinking?

36:21.048 --> 36:23.833
- How about the beach?
- Beach?

36:23.920 --> 36:26.271
- Yeah, mom loved the beach.

36:26.358 --> 36:29.056
- She did?
- Yeah.

36:31.537 --> 36:34.844
- Audrey, can we take
a rain check on Disneyland?

36:34.931 --> 36:37.804
- Can I make the sandwiches?

36:37.891 --> 36:39.109
- Yeah.

36:39.197 --> 36:41.373
Please make the sandwiches.

36:41.460 --> 36:42.504
- Okay.

36:42.852 --> 36:44.289
[buzzing continues]
- All right, you guys...

36:44.376 --> 36:48.423
you guys eat up and, um...
[buzzing stops]

36:48.510 --> 36:52.906
Eat up, and I'm gonna shower.
I'll just wash up.

36:52.993 --> 36:57.040
I went to bed so late.
All right, enjoy it.

37:07.355 --> 37:08.791
- [Audrey] You like my bear?

37:08.878 --> 37:10.184
- [Rachel] It's cute.

37:10.271 --> 37:12.360
- I told her that I hated
the beach.

37:12.447 --> 37:16.321
Couldn't stand the heat,
but I can see why she loved it.

37:16.408 --> 37:21.151
[ocean waves crushing]
[sea gulls cawing]

37:23.371 --> 37:25.068
How was it?

37:25.155 --> 37:26.722
- [Rachel] It's good,
it was cold.

37:26.809 --> 37:28.289
- [Audrey] Today, the water's
really cold.

37:28.376 --> 37:29.421
- It is?
- Yeah.

37:29.508 --> 37:31.597
- You guys hungry?
- [Rachel] Yeah.

37:31.684 --> 37:34.252
- Why don't you guys eat
something?

37:34.339 --> 37:36.036
- [Audrey] Thank you.

37:36.123 --> 37:37.429
- Thanks for making these.
- [Audrey] Yeah, of course.

37:37.516 --> 37:38.778
- They're really good.
I just had them.

37:38.865 --> 37:40.519
- [Audrey] Yeah?

37:40.606 --> 37:42.216
- [Rachel] Mom always said
you made the best sandwiches.

37:49.092 --> 37:52.879
- Ah, we should head back
in a little bit, right?

37:53.836 --> 37:56.448
[birds chirping]

37:57.884 --> 38:00.800
[car engine roaring]

38:17.817 --> 38:19.340
Guys, get in the house.

38:19.427 --> 38:20.689
- [Rachel] Who is that?

38:20.776 --> 38:22.604
- It's just a work thing.
Get in the house.

38:22.691 --> 38:24.606
Go straight to your room.

38:25.912 --> 38:26.826
Go ahead.

38:26.913 --> 38:28.001
[dramatic music]

38:28.088 --> 38:29.176
- Boss wants to see you.

38:29.263 --> 38:31.744
[dramatic music]

38:31.831 --> 38:35.661
- You know how long
I've been waiting here?

38:35.748 --> 38:37.489
A long fucking time,
that's how long.

38:37.576 --> 38:39.317
[car door closes]

38:39.404 --> 38:40.318
- I'm sorry.

38:43.233 --> 38:46.498
- Just, uh, busting your balls,
kid.

38:46.585 --> 38:48.717
I'm sorry for your loss.

38:48.804 --> 38:49.762
I really am.

38:52.504 --> 38:54.070
If anything you need, I, uh...

38:57.291 --> 38:58.292
- I'm okay, thank you.

38:58.379 --> 39:01.034
[dramatic music]

39:02.470 --> 39:03.210
Cried yet?

39:04.385 --> 39:05.125
- Cry?

39:06.779 --> 39:09.521
- You should find a spot.

39:09.608 --> 39:11.131
Just let it all out.

39:12.611 --> 39:14.917
Maybe in your car,
maybe in....

39:16.092 --> 39:17.180
in the shower.

39:17.267 --> 39:19.748
Showers are great for crying.

39:19.835 --> 39:22.447
[inhales sharply]

39:22.969 --> 39:25.841
Um...I asked, uh, Harvey, uh,

39:27.887 --> 39:32.413
for an update, and he told me
that he couldn't reach you.

39:34.284 --> 39:36.199
- Sorry about that. It's...

39:36.286 --> 39:38.724
I took the girls
to the beach to get some food,

39:38.811 --> 39:40.073
get some fresh air,

39:40.160 --> 39:42.554
so I didn't pick up my phone.

39:42.641 --> 39:44.338
- Uh...

39:44.425 --> 39:45.252
listen...

39:47.602 --> 39:51.780
You take some time,
get your head straight,

39:51.867 --> 39:54.130
do what you need to do
and when you're ready,

39:54.217 --> 39:55.218
you'll get...

39:56.655 --> 39:57.569
Back to work.

39:57.656 --> 40:00.920
[dramatic music]

40:01.007 --> 40:01.921
- Thank you.

40:03.662 --> 40:04.402
- And, uh...

40:04.489 --> 40:07.143
[dramatic music]

40:08.884 --> 40:10.625
- No, no, I can't.
I can't take that.

40:10.712 --> 40:13.672
- Oh, come on. Come on.

40:13.759 --> 40:17.545
Get those kids
some pizza or something.

40:17.632 --> 40:18.894
- Okay.

40:18.981 --> 40:21.288
Gangsters are a funny breed.

40:21.375 --> 40:23.725
Some of the nicest guys
you'll ever meet.

40:23.812 --> 40:25.988
You almost forget that
they're stone cold killers.

40:26.075 --> 40:26.902
- And, uh, Sammy...

40:29.078 --> 40:30.819
you stay reachable.

40:30.906 --> 40:32.299
- Yes, sir.

40:32.386 --> 40:33.866
Almost.

40:33.953 --> 40:35.433
[car door clunking]

40:35.520 --> 40:36.303
- Go.

40:37.435 --> 40:39.437
- Shut up! This is my bear.

40:39.524 --> 40:40.960
- So what if I cry?
- Shut up!

40:41.047 --> 40:43.571
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!
What's going on?!

40:43.658 --> 40:44.703
- She killed Teddy!
- What?

40:44.790 --> 40:47.619
- It's a fucking toy, Audrey!
Grow up!

40:47.706 --> 40:49.621
- Give it to me.
Give me the teddy bear.

40:49.708 --> 40:51.144
What happened?

40:51.231 --> 40:52.362
- She's acting like
a fucking little kid!

40:52.450 --> 40:53.929
Why are you taking her side?!

40:54.016 --> 40:55.322
- Watch your mouth!
You're acting like it's your--

40:55.409 --> 40:58.499
Are you serious right now?!
What are you doing?!

40:58.586 --> 40:59.935
- I'm the one holding
the fucking bear!

41:00.022 --> 41:01.937
Both of you shut the fuck up!

41:02.024 --> 41:03.461
- Watch your language.
You're scaring your sister.

41:03.548 --> 41:05.506
Give me the teddy bear.
- She's my sister,

41:05.593 --> 41:07.377
not your daughter,
and you're not my father!

41:07.465 --> 41:09.554
You'll never be my father!

41:11.512 --> 41:13.732
Did you really think
one picnic and one ice cream

41:13.819 --> 41:15.951
was gonna fucking
fix everything?!

41:16.038 --> 41:18.258
[dramatic music]

41:19.738 --> 41:21.783
- Give me the teddy bear, Rach.

41:21.870 --> 41:23.959
- You're the reason
my mom's dead.

41:24.046 --> 41:25.047
- Rachel!

41:25.134 --> 41:27.572
[dramatic music]

41:28.703 --> 41:29.443
[door slams]

41:33.926 --> 41:35.754
- Can you fix him?

41:35.841 --> 41:38.583
[slow piano music]

41:42.543 --> 41:43.370
- It's okay.

41:43.457 --> 41:46.242
[slow piano music]

42:00.213 --> 42:02.694
[slow piano music]

42:12.660 --> 42:15.837
It's so crazy when someone's
gone, just like that,

42:15.924 --> 42:18.187
right off the face of
the earth,

42:18.274 --> 42:20.625
and all that's left are a bunch
of pictures in your phone

42:20.712 --> 42:22.627
and some shaky video footage.

42:22.714 --> 42:24.019
[slow piano music]

42:24.106 --> 42:25.543
[laughter]

42:29.503 --> 42:31.592
God, I missed her.

42:31.679 --> 42:34.421
[slow piano music]

42:49.305 --> 42:52.482
[doorbell chimes]

42:53.396 --> 42:55.616
The doorbell ringing this
early is either a delivery,

42:55.703 --> 42:57.966
Jehovah's Witness,
or bad news.

43:00.882 --> 43:01.927
[doorbell chimes]

43:02.014 --> 43:02.841
Yeah, I'm coming!

43:12.111 --> 43:13.765
This looked like bad news.

43:13.852 --> 43:14.983
- Mr. Silverman?

43:15.070 --> 43:16.463
- Yeah.

43:19.292 --> 43:22.991
- Maria Campos,
Child Protective Services.

43:23.078 --> 43:27.213
Oh, that's my guy out there,
just in case.

43:27.300 --> 43:29.171
- In case of what?

43:29.258 --> 43:30.477
- Just in case.

43:32.914 --> 43:34.437
- This is a joke, right?

43:34.524 --> 43:36.962
- This is not a joke,
Mr. Silverman.

43:37.049 --> 43:38.790
- The girls need
to come with us.

43:38.877 --> 43:40.139
I'll give you a minute to
get their things together

43:40.226 --> 43:42.141
and say your goodbyes.

43:43.011 --> 43:44.012
- No, no, no,
it's not happening.

43:44.099 --> 43:45.579
Those are my girls in there.

43:45.666 --> 43:48.538
- Actually, they're not.
Until your case is finalized,

43:48.626 --> 43:50.671
the girls need to stay
with family.

43:50.758 --> 43:52.847
This is happening.

43:52.934 --> 43:54.806
We'll schedule the evaluations
as soon as possible

43:54.893 --> 43:57.199
and get all of the paperwork
in order.

43:57.286 --> 44:00.550
Look, the best case scenario,
this is temporary.

44:00.638 --> 44:04.163
- And the worst case scenario?

44:04.250 --> 44:06.469
- Let's just see what happens.
- What happens?

44:06.556 --> 44:09.559
This woman coming into my house
talking about family, family.

44:09.647 --> 44:12.258
I'm their family.
What other family do they have?

44:12.345 --> 44:13.868
I mean, where are
they gonna stay?

44:13.955 --> 44:15.174
Their grandmother lives
in a home.

44:15.261 --> 44:16.741
- I am not at liberty to say.

44:16.828 --> 44:18.133
- There was only one
other family member

44:18.220 --> 44:19.700
I can think of at that moment.

44:19.787 --> 44:22.485
I mean, I was still a bit drunk,
but right in that moment,

44:22.572 --> 44:24.705
I had an idea.

44:24.792 --> 44:27.969
What if they--
What if they lived with family?

44:28.056 --> 44:29.536
- That's what I just said.
[laughs]

44:29.667 --> 44:31.494
- No, no. What if they lived

44:31.581 --> 44:32.582
with family here in the house,
with me?

44:32.670 --> 44:34.889
[dramatic music]

44:34.976 --> 44:38.458
- Um... Well, I mean, I guess
technically that--

44:38.676 --> 44:42.941
- Technically is good then.
Technically is good.

44:43.028 --> 44:45.291
I gotta make a phone call.
Would you come in for a minute?

44:45.378 --> 44:46.596
- [Maria] Uh, okay.

44:46.684 --> 44:49.338
- Can he stay out here?
- [Maria] Sure.

44:49.425 --> 44:50.992
- Okay, please, come.
Five minutes.

44:51.079 --> 44:53.125
I just gotta call somebody.

44:56.911 --> 44:58.391
Is there anything I can get you?

44:58.478 --> 45:00.175
- No, please don't worry
about me. I'm good, thank you.

45:00.262 --> 45:01.481
- You sure? Okay, thank you.
- Yes.

45:01.568 --> 45:03.222
-[doorbell rings]
There he is.

45:10.620 --> 45:12.318
- Hey.
- There's a huge guy on your--

45:12.405 --> 45:13.623
- I know, I know. Come inside.

45:13.711 --> 45:15.408
I gotta introduce you
to someone.

45:15.495 --> 45:17.497
- Is this grass real?
- Yeah, yeah, yeah. Come on.

45:19.151 --> 45:19.847
Come, come, come.

45:22.502 --> 45:26.245
Ah, Maria, this is Rob Fenton.

45:26.332 --> 45:29.596
This is Maria Campos
from, uh, CPS.

45:29.683 --> 45:31.729
I was telling you on the phone.
- Hi, Mr. Fenton.

45:35.036 --> 45:37.909
- Would you like something
to drink? Uh...

45:37.996 --> 45:40.215
Want some orange juice?
I'll get you some orange juice.

45:42.957 --> 45:45.917
- Oh, God,
it looks different here.

45:48.180 --> 45:50.312
- Freshly squeezed.

45:50.399 --> 45:53.751
[juice pouring]

45:57.537 --> 45:58.364
There you go.

46:00.801 --> 46:02.498
Rob, listen, Missus, uh, Miss--

46:03.761 --> 46:05.763
- Miss.
- Miss Campos is here.

46:05.850 --> 46:08.156
She's helping me
with the adoption papers.

46:08.243 --> 46:10.811
The only way the girls can
actually live here with me

46:10.898 --> 46:13.161
is if there's a family member
living here.

46:13.248 --> 46:14.162
- [Maria] That's correct.

46:14.249 --> 46:15.947
- Correct?
- Yes.

46:16.034 --> 46:18.340
- I mean, everyone's been
through so much,

46:18.427 --> 46:19.820
especially the girls.

46:19.907 --> 46:20.952
- Wow, that's really good juice.

46:21.039 --> 46:22.344
- You like that orange juice?

46:22.431 --> 46:24.520
You can have as much
orange juice as you want.

46:24.607 --> 46:26.218
- But I already have a place.

46:26.305 --> 46:28.089
- Yeah, but this is
just a couple of weeks.

46:28.176 --> 46:30.613
- Yeah, maybe more,

46:30.700 --> 46:34.182
and if the papers go through,
you know, it's a process.

46:34.269 --> 46:35.749
- If the paperwork goes through.

46:35.836 --> 46:37.359
Well, I'm sure
it's gonna go through, right?

46:37.446 --> 46:39.971
- We'll see. We just
take it one day at a time.

46:40.058 --> 46:41.189
- So it's temporary?

46:41.276 --> 46:43.278
- It's definitely temporary.

46:43.583 --> 46:44.932
[door knob clicking]

46:45.019 --> 46:46.455
- [Audrey] Uncle Rob?

46:46.542 --> 46:49.894
- [Rob] Hey, look at you.

46:49.981 --> 46:52.113
How you doing?
Oh, my God!

46:53.027 --> 46:54.681
- [Audrey]
What are you doing here?

46:54.768 --> 46:55.943
- I invited your uncle
for breakfast.

46:56.030 --> 46:58.641
- Yeah, I'm having orange juice.

46:58.728 --> 46:59.817
- Teddy's dead.

47:01.122 --> 47:04.125
- [Maria] What?
- Teddy's dead.

47:04.212 --> 47:05.344
- Who's Teddy?
- It's just...

47:06.345 --> 47:07.607
- It's nothing,
it's a teddy bear.

47:07.694 --> 47:09.435
- Ah, honey,
can you do me a favor?

47:09.522 --> 47:11.829
Can you give please give us
a minute?

47:11.916 --> 47:14.222
- We'll hang out, okay?
See you.

47:15.615 --> 47:16.529
[whispers] She's so big.

47:17.399 --> 47:19.401
- Uh, so we're good?

47:23.623 --> 47:25.233
- Yeah, we're good.

47:25.320 --> 47:28.323
- Well, I just have to
update your paperwork,

47:28.410 --> 47:30.499
but we should be good,

47:30.586 --> 47:33.111
and I'll have to run a quick
background check on Mr. Fenton.

47:33.198 --> 47:35.330
- Background check?
- Yes.

47:35.417 --> 47:37.115
We'll keep in touch,
Mr. Silverman.

47:37.202 --> 47:38.203
- [Sammy] Uh, Silver.

47:38.290 --> 47:40.031
- Right.

47:40.118 --> 47:41.989
- Okay, thank you.
So, you'll call me?

47:42.076 --> 47:42.947
- I will.

47:43.034 --> 47:44.078
- Okay, great.

47:45.471 --> 47:47.777
I worked very hard to stay clean
on paper.

47:47.865 --> 47:50.563
You look me up anywhere and
I'm basically squeaky clean,

47:50.650 --> 47:51.912
but this guy...

47:51.999 --> 47:53.696
You're clean?

47:53.783 --> 47:55.524
- Yeah. I got allergies.

47:55.611 --> 47:57.657
- Allergies?
- That's why I'm sniffing.

47:57.744 --> 47:59.267
- Okay, good.
- Yeah.

47:59.354 --> 48:01.791
- Rachel! Your uncle's here!
- Rachel's here?

48:01.879 --> 48:04.838
- Yeah, sit,
I'll tell you everything.

48:04.925 --> 48:07.667
- Uncle Rob.
- [laughs]

48:07.754 --> 48:09.234
- What are you doing here?

48:09.321 --> 48:11.018
- [Rob] I'm hanging.

48:11.584 --> 48:13.325
- [both] Brr! [laughing]

48:13.412 --> 48:14.804
You'll get it next time.

48:14.892 --> 48:16.241
- What are you doing here?

48:16.328 --> 48:17.982
- Hanging out, yeah.

48:18.069 --> 48:19.331
- [Sammy] Your uncle's gonna
live with us.

48:19.418 --> 48:21.289
- Really?
- For a little bit, yeah.

48:21.376 --> 48:23.988
- Oh, that's awesome.
I'm gonna go brush my teeth.

48:24.075 --> 48:26.033
- Okay.
I wasn't gonna say anything.

48:26.120 --> 48:27.513
- [Sammy] All right.

48:27.600 --> 48:28.993
- [Rachel] Shut up.

48:32.344 --> 48:34.259
- It's crazy how much
she looks like her.

48:34.346 --> 48:35.564
- It's crazy. Hey...

48:35.651 --> 48:39.307
I really appreciate
you doing this.

48:39.394 --> 48:41.048
It means a lot.

48:41.135 --> 48:42.920
- I'd do anything for them.
- I know.

48:45.183 --> 48:46.836
I'll get you set up.

48:46.924 --> 48:48.403
If you need anything,
just let me know.

48:48.490 --> 48:49.578
- [Rob] Okay.
- All right?

48:49.665 --> 48:52.973
- Mm-hmm.
- Thank you. Appreciate it.

48:53.060 --> 48:54.975
All I knew about Rob is
that he loved his sister,

48:55.062 --> 48:57.064
and she loved him.

48:57.151 --> 48:59.762
Now I gotta go hide
all my valuables.

48:59.849 --> 49:01.939
- You guys got any coffee?

49:04.724 --> 49:07.031
What? No?

49:07.422 --> 49:09.468
- Yeah, black okay?

49:09.555 --> 49:10.556
- Please.

49:14.473 --> 49:17.389
[coffee pouring]

49:17.476 --> 49:19.304
You guys don't eat ever?

49:24.352 --> 49:26.833
[mug clunks]

49:29.140 --> 49:31.359
[dramatic music]

49:31.446 --> 49:33.144
God, Rachel.

49:33.231 --> 49:35.233
It's crazy how much
you look like her.

49:35.320 --> 49:37.235
Sammy, right?

49:37.322 --> 49:39.063
[dramatic music]

49:40.151 --> 49:42.196
- Yeah, you really do.

49:43.284 --> 49:45.460
- I'm not her.

49:45.547 --> 49:48.463
- I know, I didn't...
I didn't mean it like that.

49:48.550 --> 49:50.291
- I know what you meant.

49:51.945 --> 49:53.251
Audrey looks like Dad.

49:55.209 --> 49:57.864
It's hard to forget someone
when you see them every day.

49:57.951 --> 50:01.824
- Well, you're not supposed
to forget.

50:01.911 --> 50:05.132
You're supposed to remember.
- Yeah, well, remembering sucks.

50:05.219 --> 50:08.135
[dramatic music]

50:08.222 --> 50:10.659
- I'm gonna make some coffee.

50:10.746 --> 50:12.531
You guys want some, Rachel?

50:12.792 --> 50:13.619
- No, I'm good.

50:18.493 --> 50:21.670
- All right, movie marathon
tonight, yeah?

50:21.757 --> 50:25.283
We stay up late,
popcorn, burping, farting.

50:25.370 --> 50:26.719
She's been farting all night,
so--

50:26.806 --> 50:29.678
- No, that was Teddy's corpse.

50:29.765 --> 50:31.245
- Teddy's?
- It's his ghost, yeah.

50:32.681 --> 50:33.291
- Excuses.
- Mm-hmm.

50:34.509 --> 50:36.250
- It's a school night

50:36.337 --> 50:38.165
- School?

50:38.252 --> 50:43.040
Don't you guys get, like,
time to grieve and stuff?

50:44.302 --> 50:45.520
- No.

50:46.043 --> 50:47.305
- [Sammy] They missed
enough school already.

50:47.392 --> 50:49.437
- It's one more day, Sammy.

50:49.524 --> 50:51.178
What's the difference?

50:52.397 --> 50:54.660
- Can we, please?

50:55.574 --> 50:57.097
- What a nightmare.

50:57.228 --> 50:59.969
I was trying to move a few steps
forward with these kids,

51:00.057 --> 51:01.319
and he was knocking me
10 steps back

51:01.406 --> 51:04.148
every time he opened his mouth.

51:04.235 --> 51:06.541
You guys can do marathon night
on the weekend.

51:06.628 --> 51:09.066
- How about that?
- This weekend?

51:09.153 --> 51:11.546
It's like Tuesday.
- Whatever.

51:11.633 --> 51:14.027
- But I had an Ace up my sleeve.

51:14.114 --> 51:16.247
This should definitely work.

51:19.815 --> 51:22.340
I really gotta stop drinking.

51:27.606 --> 51:30.217
All right, here we are.

51:30.304 --> 51:32.306
- You guys all set?
- Yeah.

51:32.393 --> 51:34.003
All right, I'll pick
you guys up later,

51:34.091 --> 51:35.831
and we'll go have dinner
wherever you want.

51:35.918 --> 51:37.355
- Okay.
- Okay.

51:37.442 --> 51:38.443
- Bye, Sammy.

51:38.530 --> 51:39.444
- Bye, Audrey.

51:44.013 --> 51:45.406
- You know, next time
you take us to school,

51:45.493 --> 51:48.105
how about you drop us off
on time?

51:48.192 --> 51:49.845
- [Sammy] Sorry.
- It's okay.

51:52.152 --> 51:55.677
[cellphone buzzing]
- Yo.

51:55.764 --> 51:57.375
- I've been calling you
for two days,

51:57.462 --> 51:58.767
and this is how you answer, eh?

51:58.854 --> 52:01.118
- I'm sorry. I'm just
so busy with these girls.

52:01.205 --> 52:02.684
- No, no, I understand
that, son, all right?

52:02.771 --> 52:05.252
But this is important,
all right?

52:05.339 --> 52:07.863
We need to talk.
- About what?

52:07.950 --> 52:10.039
- Something big, Sammy.

52:10.997 --> 52:11.780
- Okay.

52:13.304 --> 52:15.088
All right, give me like
30 minutes.

52:16.045 --> 52:19.048
[sighs]

52:25.142 --> 52:26.578
- [Harvey] Hey.
- Hey.

52:30.886 --> 52:31.974
How you doing?

52:34.151 --> 52:36.370
You got me rushing over here.

52:41.114 --> 52:44.900
- You know how you make
the perfect cup of tea?

52:44.987 --> 52:46.641
- [Sammy] What?

52:46.728 --> 52:48.121
- Timing.

52:50.993 --> 52:52.212
Go ahead and open it.

52:52.299 --> 52:53.909
- What is it?

52:53.996 --> 52:55.694
- [Harvey] You'll see.

52:58.262 --> 53:00.307
Omar Al Said.

53:00.394 --> 53:02.048
- I don't know who that is.

53:02.266 --> 53:03.528
- You're not supposed to know
who he is.

53:03.615 --> 53:05.312
What you need to know
is what he has

53:05.399 --> 53:07.358
hanging on his walls.

53:09.142 --> 53:11.013
That piece sold to
an anonymous buyer last year

53:11.100 --> 53:13.538
for a little over $50 mil,
all right?

53:13.625 --> 53:16.628
The art world is crawling
with rich lunatics,

53:16.715 --> 53:18.978
and I got one ready
to take that off our hands

53:19.065 --> 53:20.632
once it is in our hands.

53:20.719 --> 53:23.852
- $50 million.
What's our take?

53:23.939 --> 53:29.293
- I haven't figured it all out
yet, but it's gonna be big.

53:29.380 --> 53:32.339
- I'm sure a guy like that has
a lot of security with him.

53:32.426 --> 53:33.993
- Mm. Well, stake it out,
all right?

53:34.080 --> 53:35.995
See what your balls say.

53:36.082 --> 53:37.562
There's always a way
around them, you know?

53:37.649 --> 53:38.998
Always is.

53:39.216 --> 53:42.393
- I hated to admit it,
but the old man was right.

53:42.480 --> 53:45.004
This could be the job
to end all jobs.

53:45.091 --> 53:47.354
The take could be $5 million
easy,

53:47.441 --> 53:49.965
but bigger paydays
come with bigger risks.

53:52.403 --> 53:53.708
- Oh, it's terrible.

53:53.795 --> 53:57.582
- Yeah, of course.
You waited too long, huh?

53:58.974 --> 54:00.933
You now, your mother got me
into tea.

54:01.020 --> 54:03.718
I was a pure coffee guy
when we met.

54:03.805 --> 54:05.720
Black, no fucking around.

54:07.853 --> 54:10.551
Yeah, she changed me
in many ways,

54:10.638 --> 54:12.945
and some things
she couldn't change.

54:13.032 --> 54:14.425
- Pop, let me ask you,

54:14.512 --> 54:16.601
how did you ever tell her
about the business?

54:16.731 --> 54:18.994
- I didn't. She found out.

54:19.081 --> 54:20.953
- Wait, I thought you told her.
That's why she left.

54:21.040 --> 54:22.302
- No, she found out.

54:22.389 --> 54:24.870
She was more hurt
that I didn't tell her

54:24.957 --> 54:29.309
what I was doing than
she was about what I was doing.

54:29.396 --> 54:30.832
You know, Sammy, once trust
goes out the door,

54:30.919 --> 54:33.487
everything else follows.

54:33.574 --> 54:34.880
- You never thought about
walking away?

54:34.967 --> 54:36.621
- Oh, no.

54:36.708 --> 54:38.144
This is all I know.

54:39.667 --> 54:42.627
I never wanted you
to be part of this life,

54:42.714 --> 54:46.239
but I didn't want to
hide it from you either,

54:46.326 --> 54:49.460
and now this is all you know.

54:52.158 --> 54:54.900
But you know you have
a choice to make now, son.

54:57.598 --> 54:58.991
- I think I know.

55:01.341 --> 55:03.952
This looks great, Dad.

55:04.039 --> 55:07.304
- This, we pull off...

55:07.391 --> 55:09.001
you don't have to worry.

55:09.088 --> 55:12.352
We take care of those kids,
take care of Ira,

55:12.439 --> 55:14.615
have the life you want.

55:15.355 --> 55:18.315
- That's exactly what
I've been looking for.

55:18.402 --> 55:22.362
I appreciate it, Pop. You always
look out for me, you really do.

55:22.449 --> 55:23.842
Love you, Pop. Bye.

55:23.929 --> 55:25.626
I'll take a look at this,
and I'll call you.

55:25.713 --> 55:28.586
[dramatic music]

55:34.331 --> 55:39.074
[car engine roaring]
[dramatic music]

55:50.477 --> 55:53.306
A gate is usually a good sign.

55:53.393 --> 55:55.830
It means big house
with big money,

55:55.917 --> 55:58.224
but it also means big trouble.

56:00.661 --> 56:02.315
Getting on the other side
of that gate,

56:02.402 --> 56:03.838
it's gonna be
a fucking nightmare.

56:03.925 --> 56:06.319
[dramatic music]

56:06.406 --> 56:08.234
Hello?
- [Principal] Mr. Silverman.

56:08.321 --> 56:10.149
- What?

56:10.236 --> 56:11.977
- [Principal] I need you to
come to the school right now.

56:12.064 --> 56:12.934
- Okay, I'm coming.

56:13.021 --> 56:16.329
[dramatic music]

56:16.416 --> 56:21.160
[car engine roaring]
[dramatic music]

56:22.988 --> 56:25.599
[dramatic music]

56:30.648 --> 56:31.605
- Follow me.

56:31.692 --> 56:34.303
[dramatic music]

56:37.742 --> 56:39.004
- What exactly did she do?

56:39.091 --> 56:40.658
- She vandalized
school property.

56:40.745 --> 56:42.834
She broke into
the gym's equipment locker

56:42.921 --> 56:46.881
and then punctured every single
one of the school's basketballs

56:46.968 --> 56:48.274
with this.

56:48.361 --> 56:51.016
Is this from your home,
Mr. Silverman?

56:51.103 --> 56:53.061
- Yeah, that's mine.

56:53.366 --> 56:56.151
- Normally, I would push
for immediate suspension

56:56.238 --> 56:57.849
or even expulsion,

56:57.936 --> 57:00.678
but considering
the recent tragic circumstances

57:00.765 --> 57:01.940
and the fact that, Rachel,

57:02.027 --> 57:04.246
you've always been
a fine student,

57:04.333 --> 57:06.335
I'm gonna show
some leniency here.

57:06.423 --> 57:08.294
- Thank you.

57:08.381 --> 57:10.775
- You'll be getting
a bill for all the damages.

57:10.862 --> 57:12.472
It'll do some good for Rachel
to stay home

57:12.559 --> 57:16.041
for a couple more days,
and her sister, too.

57:17.042 --> 57:18.739
- What does Audrey
have to do with this?

57:18.826 --> 57:21.481
- They're hurting.
They need to stay home.

57:21.568 --> 57:23.918
They need to take this all in.

57:24.049 --> 57:26.268
- I know she knows better
than this,

57:26.355 --> 57:29.054
but, um, just send me the bill,

57:29.141 --> 57:31.926
and I'll take care of it,
and I really appreciate it.

57:33.841 --> 57:35.887
- Can we please go home now?

57:35.974 --> 57:36.757
- Yeah.

57:39.107 --> 57:41.936
Thank you. I'm sorry.

57:42.023 --> 57:43.677
It won't happen again.

57:48.595 --> 57:50.945
Rach, why the basketballs?

57:52.338 --> 57:55.254
- Yeah, why did you do that?
I thought you loved basketball.

57:55.341 --> 57:57.212
- She does?
- Yeah.

57:57.299 --> 57:59.954
- You do?
- Not anymore.

58:00.041 --> 58:01.434
- You know how much trouble
you're in?

58:01.521 --> 58:03.610
You know how much money
this is gonna cost me?

58:03.697 --> 58:06.178
Do you have any idea how much
money it's gonna cost me?

58:06.265 --> 58:07.527
- I honestly don't care.

58:23.325 --> 58:24.065
[door slams]

58:31.116 --> 58:32.552
- Straight to your room.

58:38.558 --> 58:41.430
[ice cube clunking]

58:46.610 --> 58:47.393
Rob!

58:49.830 --> 58:52.485
The thing about ex junkies
is a nine out of 10,

58:52.572 --> 58:55.053
their old habits never die.

58:55.140 --> 58:55.923
Rob?

58:58.186 --> 59:00.537
It's just a matter of
opportunity and a matter of time

59:00.624 --> 59:03.583
before history
starts repeating itself.

59:14.986 --> 59:16.988
Hey, put your feet down.

59:19.773 --> 59:21.209
What are you doing?

59:22.428 --> 59:24.561
- Just, uh, I'm just regrouping.

59:27.172 --> 59:28.695
- You high?

59:31.480 --> 59:33.352
Are you high?

59:33.439 --> 59:36.007
- [exhaling]

59:36.094 --> 59:37.574
I think I'm sunstroke.

59:37.661 --> 59:39.053
I've been out here for hours.

59:39.140 --> 59:41.578
- Sunstroke?
- Yeah.

59:41.665 --> 59:44.058
- Maybe it's your allergies,
huh?

59:44.145 --> 59:47.279
- Yeah, I mean,
these trees, the flowers,

59:47.366 --> 59:50.587
the pollens in the pool.
You know?

59:51.109 --> 59:53.067
Could be it.

59:53.154 --> 59:55.374
- CPS shows up, and they see
you high as a fucking kite,

59:55.461 --> 59:57.506
what do you think
they're gonna do?

59:57.594 --> 59:59.030
The only reason these girls
get to live here

59:59.117 --> 1:00:00.771
is because you're here.

1:00:00.858 --> 1:00:02.599
What are you thinking?

1:00:05.123 --> 1:00:06.733
- I didn't take that much.

1:00:06.820 --> 1:00:08.953
- You didn't take much.

1:00:09.040 --> 1:00:12.696
Well, I'm sorry
I'm overreacting here.

1:00:12.783 --> 1:00:14.523
You want these girls
to see you like this?

1:00:14.611 --> 1:00:16.482
Cool Uncle Rob?

1:00:16.569 --> 1:00:18.310
High as a fucking kite?

1:00:20.181 --> 1:00:22.270
I don't want drugs
in this house, do you hear me?

1:00:22.357 --> 1:00:24.098
I'm gonna fucking fix up
your nose and your pocket

1:00:24.185 --> 1:00:25.534
and the living room.

1:00:25.839 --> 1:00:27.841
This is a no drug zone.
You can't follow those rules,

1:00:27.928 --> 1:00:30.104
you need to get the fuck out.

1:00:32.063 --> 1:00:32.803
Wake up.

1:00:35.849 --> 1:00:37.242
Rachel!

1:00:43.161 --> 1:00:45.598
- [Audrey] Good night.
- [Rachel] Good night.

1:00:45.685 --> 1:00:47.382
Are we going to the movies
tomorrow like you promised?

1:00:47.469 --> 1:00:49.515
- [Sammy] Yeah, yeah,
I swear, tomorrow.

1:00:49.602 --> 1:00:51.430
- [Rachel] Promise?
- [Sammy] I promise.

1:00:51.517 --> 1:00:53.084
- [Rachel] Okay.
- [Sammy] We'll do it tomorrow.

1:00:53.171 --> 1:00:54.781
- [Audrey] All right.
- [Rachel] Good night.

1:00:54.868 --> 1:00:56.217
- [Sammy] Goodnight.
- [Rachel] Good night.

1:01:14.018 --> 1:01:15.236
- It's all gone.

1:01:16.455 --> 1:01:17.282
I'm off it.

1:01:18.892 --> 1:01:20.720
- Mazel Tov.

1:01:24.071 --> 1:01:27.379
- You know, alcohol is a pretty
big vice, just saying.

1:01:29.860 --> 1:01:31.600
- It's better than crack.

1:01:31.688 --> 1:01:33.864
- Yeah, it's not crack.

1:01:33.951 --> 1:01:35.169
Mind if I...

1:01:36.518 --> 1:01:38.129
- Knock yourself out.

1:01:39.434 --> 1:01:40.697
- Just a little.

1:01:44.178 --> 1:01:45.789
[alcohol pouring]

1:01:51.969 --> 1:01:55.276
Ooh. God,
I think I'll stick to crack.

1:01:55.363 --> 1:01:57.626
[chuckles]

1:01:58.627 --> 1:02:01.587
You know, my sister always knew
what to say.

1:02:01.674 --> 1:02:05.243
She always knew what to do
to get me off that shit.

1:02:05.330 --> 1:02:11.205
With just a few words,
I'd be off it, cold turkey.

1:02:13.294 --> 1:02:18.473
Till I wasn't, of course,
but she never gave up on me.

1:02:18.560 --> 1:02:20.606
She always stood by me,

1:02:20.693 --> 1:02:24.262
and she'd say a few things
and I'd be off of it again.

1:02:25.742 --> 1:02:28.005
- Your sister was tired, Rob.

1:02:29.397 --> 1:02:31.008
- Yeah, I know.

1:02:31.095 --> 1:02:32.357
- I mean...

1:02:34.011 --> 1:02:36.491
She tried everything.
You always came back.

1:02:36.578 --> 1:02:38.189
You always went back.

1:02:39.712 --> 1:02:42.149
- She was stronger than
all of us, right?

1:02:43.629 --> 1:02:44.369
- Yeah.

1:02:46.066 --> 1:02:48.025
Yes, she was.

1:02:49.635 --> 1:02:50.462
- To Laura.

1:02:54.379 --> 1:02:55.249
[clink]

1:02:58.470 --> 1:03:01.560
[inhales, exhales]

1:03:04.215 --> 1:03:05.956
I fucking miss her, man.

1:03:12.701 --> 1:03:14.312
- Me too.

1:03:21.754 --> 1:03:23.364
Those girls miss her.

1:03:25.105 --> 1:03:26.846
- [Rob] Yeah, but you're
doing a good job with them.

1:03:26.933 --> 1:03:27.934
You really are.

1:03:28.021 --> 1:03:30.676
[dramatic music]

1:03:31.764 --> 1:03:32.721
- I'm trying.

1:03:32.809 --> 1:03:35.463
[dramatic music]

1:03:38.249 --> 1:03:42.993
[car engine roaring]
[dramatic music]

1:03:52.785 --> 1:03:54.134
After very little thought,

1:03:54.221 --> 1:03:57.268
I decided to take
the painting job.

1:03:57.355 --> 1:03:58.747
"Decided" was an understatement.

1:03:58.835 --> 1:04:01.533
[dramatic music]

1:04:01.620 --> 1:04:03.665
[camera shutters]

1:04:03.752 --> 1:04:06.668
[dramatic music]

1:04:07.669 --> 1:04:10.063
- [Richie] How many you see?
- Two.

1:04:11.978 --> 1:04:12.892
- Look again.

1:04:12.979 --> 1:04:15.634
[dramatic music]

1:04:20.378 --> 1:04:22.032
Still?
- Yeah.

1:04:22.119 --> 1:04:23.207
- All right.

1:04:24.686 --> 1:04:26.427
It's gonna be easier
to go over the wall

1:04:26.514 --> 1:04:29.648
than go over that fence.
Just saying.

1:04:29.735 --> 1:04:31.563
- All right,
let's get outta here.

1:04:31.650 --> 1:04:33.608
I brought the genius
with me for the first stakeout

1:04:33.695 --> 1:04:36.263
and quickly realized that
if this was gonna work,

1:04:36.350 --> 1:04:39.049
I was gonna need a proper crew.

1:04:40.180 --> 1:04:42.139
Harvey hooked me up with lunch
and a lead.

1:04:42.226 --> 1:04:44.924
- There's David Dallas
from Milwaukee.

1:04:45.011 --> 1:04:46.491
He's in town for
a little business,

1:04:46.578 --> 1:04:49.407
but he's always up for
a little something on the side.

1:04:49.494 --> 1:04:51.278
- [Sammy] David Dallas.
You wouldn't know it

1:04:51.365 --> 1:04:53.977
by looking at this guy,
but Dallas was military,

1:04:54.064 --> 1:04:55.587
trained killer.

1:04:55.674 --> 1:04:57.241
If anyone can help us
with our security problems,

1:04:57.328 --> 1:04:58.372
it was Dallas.

1:04:58.459 --> 1:05:01.680
- Excusez-moi, mademoiselle.

1:05:01.767 --> 1:05:06.337
When you have a moment, no rush,
I would like another espresso.

1:05:06.424 --> 1:05:07.991
Merci.

1:05:08.078 --> 1:05:10.167
- [Sammy]
Great guy, amazing manners,

1:05:10.254 --> 1:05:11.995
but if you were
on his shit list,

1:05:12.082 --> 1:05:13.648
his sweet disposition
went out the window.

1:05:13.735 --> 1:05:16.608
[dramatic music]

1:05:16.695 --> 1:05:18.044
With all fairness, if Dallas
showed up at your door

1:05:18.131 --> 1:05:20.177
unannounced, you had it coming.

1:05:20.264 --> 1:05:22.309
